From afef18a2817580b677d27819c548f03c3260fcfc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vincenzo@igrimaldi.engineering>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 14:17:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(arm-library): sliding conveyor feed, aligned pick/drop,
 offset pallet, safety cell

- Conveyor cartons now slide continuously toward the pick point (per-frame
  ref-driven), one arriving each cycle, instead of jumping between slots.
- Pick/drop aligned to the belt: a carton sits at the pick point before the
  grab, hands off to the gripper, and lands at the optimizer's exact target.
- Realistic cell layout: arm base at a pallet corner, pallet offset in +X so it
  is beside the arm (not underneath), conveyor on the -X side.
- Safety fence perimeter + andon light tower (green building / blue done),
  wider camera framing to fit the cell.

Schematic primitives (no CAD/GLB). Typecheck clean; parity PASS; no engine change.
